title: 1bd/1ba Peaceful Clean Apartment in Minneapolis, Solar Powered! 9/1
posting_body: ['Available 9/1 or earlier!', 'Eco-friendly property company providing quality, affordable housing.', 'Equipped with an electric vehicle charging station, 1600 Park features large windows with heat reflective coatings, as well as privacy coatings on all surface level windows.', 'All laundry machines are free to use.', 'Green Rock provides laundry detergent, hand/body soap, bathroom tile scrub, LED light bulbs, dog waste bags, and compost bags free for tenants.', 'These products are locally sourced, saving the tenants money and reducing waste at the same time!', 'Sophisticated recycling services located on site, accommodating textile, battery/electronics, plastic bag, styrofoam, metal, and light bulb recycling!', '40,000 Watt Solar Panel array to be installed soon!', 'Recently renovated building.', 'This 500 sqft unit features hickory cabinets, recycled paperstone countertops, stainless steel stove/microwave, and refrigerator, through-wall air conditioning unit, and laminate wood flooring.', 'Quiet and clean building with beautiful landscaping.', 'Located just south of downtown Minneapolis, this property has convenient access to bus routes 9, 17, and 5, with plenty of restaurants, coffee shops, and shopping areas nearby!', 'Enjoy all that downtown has to offer, while residing in a quiet pocket of the busy city.', 'Utilities paid by tenants: Electricity                Utilities paid by owner: Gas, Water, Trash/Compost, Internet', 'Gym facilities located at neighboring building.', 'Community garden owned and managed by Green Rock available for tenants located just a block away.', 'This property is pet friendly for cats and dogs, pending owner approval, with additional pet deposit and rent.', 'Off-street parking available for additional fee.', 'To view availability, schedule a showing, and apply, visit: <URL>', 'This unit is part of the Minneapolis affordable housing program (4D).', 'This means that rents are capped at certain limits, and occupants must make less than 60% of the AMI (area median income).', "Maximum rents for 1 bedroom units in 2022-2023 is $1,320 and occupant's AGI (adjusted gross income) must not exceed $49,320 for one person, $55,340 for two people, and $63,360 for three people.", 'You can learn more about the 4D program here: https://www2.minneapolismn.gov/government/programs-initiatives/housing-development-assistance/rental-property/4d/']
